main event: A high school student observed an oval-shaped object, as large as a quarter when observed through binoculars, for 1 hour and 20 minutes. The object was white in color and eventually faded out.
interesting points: The observation was made using binoculars by a high school student, adding a level of credibility to the sighting.
The object was observed for a significant duration of time, allowing for detailed study.
Wind direction and velocities were noted to coincide with the travel of the object, leading to the conclusion that it was most likely a balloon.
The report contains diagrams of a saucer-like object with annotations, adding visual data to the observation.
Although initially reported as traveling from North to West, there were conflicting statements about the object's course, indicating some ambiguity in the observation.
sighted object: Oval-shaped object, white in color, as large as a quarter when observed through binoculars
location: Floyd Bennett Navy AB, New York
